data.text:
Long time friends and musical partners David Binney & Kenny Wollesen went into Brooklyn's famed Figure 8 Studios in February of 2020 to record a duo album. Kenny brought his electric vibes, drums and hand made instruments known as Wollesonics and Dave played saxophones and Figure 8's impressive synth and organ collection. Michael Coleman engineered the session plus added live effects and electric piano. Dave mixed and mastered the recording in his studio in LA- Future Philosophy.

David Binney-Saxophones, Synths, Vocal, Production, Mix, Master

Kenny Wollesen-Drums, Synth Drums, E-Vibes, Percussion, Wollesonics

Michael Prince Coleman-Engineer, Live Effects, electric piano

Recorded at Figure 8 Studios, Brooklyn mid-Feb 2020

Post Produced, Mixed, Mastered by David Binney at Future Philosophy Los Angeles June/July 2020

Soon after Jonas Mekas left this world, his close friends – the Gang – with whom he sang many songs, felt the urge to send him a message of love. And so was born this 7-inch vinyl entitled “Song for Jonas.”

The Gang performed this composition live at Jonas’ memorial at St. Mark's Church in New York City in the Spring of 2019 and shortly after recorded it at EastSide Sound studios. Each vinyl cover is unique and hand silk screened with the first 100 personally colored by the members of the Gang. The music was inspired by Lithuanian folk tradition. Proceeds from the sales of this record will go towards maintaining the Jonas Mekas Estate. Edition of 500.
